author: A.J. Baime
title: One Little Red Corvette Leads to Another
text:
Kim Burroughs, 43, a dentist from Gambrills, Md., on her 1962 Chevrolet Corvette, as told to A.J. Baime.
When I was little, my sister and I both had Barbie dolls and Barbie Corvettes, which were toy cars that Barbie “drove.” Mine was purple, my sister’s was silver, and we played with them all the time.
